From: Paulo Alcantara <pc@cjr.nz>
Date: Sat, 28 Nov 2020 16:54:02 -0300
Subject: [PATCH] cifs: fix potential use-after-free in cifs_echo_request()
References: bsc#1012628
Patch-mainline: 5.9.14
Git-commit: 212253367dc7b49ed3fc194ce71b0992eacaecf2

commit 212253367dc7b49ed3fc194ce71b0992eacaecf2 upstream.

This patch fixes a potential use-after-free bug in
cifs_echo_request().

For instance,

  thread 1
  --------
  cifs_demultiplex_thread()
    clean_demultiplex_info()
      kfree(server)

  thread 2 (workqueue)
  --------
  apic_timer_interrupt()
    smp_apic_timer_interrupt()
      irq_exit()
        __do_softirq()
          run_timer_softirq()
            call_timer_fn()
	      cifs_echo_request() <- use-after-free in server ptr

Signed-off-by: Paulo Alcantara (SUSE) <pc@cjr.nz>
CC: Stable <stable@vger.kernel.org>
Reviewed-by: Ronnie Sahlberg <lsahlber@redhat.com>
Signed-off-by: Steve French <stfrench@microsoft.com>
Signed-off-by: Greg Kroah-Hartman <gregkh@linuxfoundation.org>
Signed-off-by: Jiri Slaby <jslaby@suse.cz>
---
 fs/cifs/connect.c | 2 ++
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+)

diff --git a/fs/cifs/connect.c b/fs/cifs/connect.c
index b8780a79a42a..cc524e31e449 100644
--- a/fs/cifs/connect.c
+++ b/fs/cifs/connect.c
@@ -935,6 +935,8 @@ static void clean_demultiplex_info(struct TCP_Server_Info *server)
 	list_del_init(&server->tcp_ses_list);
 	spin_unlock(&cifs_tcp_ses_lock);
 
+	cancel_delayed_work_sync(&server->echo);
+
 	spin_lock(&GlobalMid_Lock);
 	server->tcpStatus = CifsExiting;
 	spin_unlock(&GlobalMid_Lock);
